 Support, through expertise, all relevant functions by providing an analysis of the applicable constraints, by alerting where appropriate to the risks and by proposing solutions that comply with the regulations in force.
 Support business priorities by assessing all requirements for classification of supplies and technologies used (both internal and external), license applications needed for import and export, and by screening the stakeholders involved;
 Analyze the regulatory constraints and risks on each transaction involving the business or its staff, share as necessary with the entity’s Legal Director and the BL’s Trade Compliance Manager to support the strategy to be put in place, and independently address the targeted constraints while protecting the BL and its staff;
 Contribute, under the responsibility of the entity’s Legal Director or the BL’s Trade Compliance Manager, to relations with competent authorities and stakeholders. In particular, to be the interface with national and international supervisory authorities for matters involving his or her scope, where appropriate in agreement with the entity’s Director of Legal or the BL’s Trade Compliance Officer;
 Ensure traceability of operations carried out in accordance with the regulations in force (signing contracts, taking orders, exports, transfers, etc.) and consolidate within his or her scope the reports intended for the authorities;
 Identify, plan and conduct the necessary training and awareness activities on his or her own;
 Exercise a duty to inform by notifying the entity’s Legal Director or the BL’s Trade Compliance
