9
As a member of the team, you will leverage your deep understanding of market abuse patterns—including insider trading, layering, spoofing, front-running, and manipulation—across multiple asset classes such as FX, Fixed Income, Commodities, and Rates. You’ll be responsible for designing and developing robust surveillance scenarios from the ground up and ensuring these are tailored to both regulatory and business needs. Your role will require creating clear Business Requirement Documents (BRDs), drafting policies and procedures, and collaborating with stakeholders across compliance, trading, IT, and audit functions to ensure holistic and actionable surveillance solutions. You will be tasked with tuning and calibrating surveillance parameters to optimize detection and reduce false positives, and you’ll provide subject matter expertise throughout the trade lifecycle—from transaction capture to reporting—while staying abreast of evolving regulatory expectations and best practices. The position demands a proactive approach to identifying process or governance gaps and contributing to the ongoing evolution of policies as market behaviors, products, and regulations change. Through these activities, you will play a critical part in maintaining the integrity of market operations and supporting clients in meeting both their compliance obligations and strategic objectives.
